@component watchdog
@intent Always-on liveness watchdog (deps-0) for the live board. Guards the WS **server** and the **main bridge**, auto-restarting either if it dies — the infrastructure guarantee behind "always connected": if this stays detached-resident, the board survives individual session ends. Watches by holding a `board`-role WS connection (connect succeeds = server alive); on WS drop/connect-fail it re-checks TCP, restarts server.cjs if down, and reconnects with backoff; when the pushed AgentList lacks the main agent it restarts the bridge. A 15s backup timer revives the server if WS stays disconnected. Non-interrupt principle: never touches a live server/bridge — only spawns a replacement when one is dead, with a per-target SPAWN_COOLDOWN to avoid duplicate spawns during startup. Single-instance principle: a port-scoped PID lock at boot rejects a second watchdog (two watchdogs racing the same targets bypass the cooldown and double-subscribe AgentList). Restarts are detached (survive the watchdog's own death). Pure runtime, no DOM. (Distilled from dashboard/live/ws-watchdog.cjs — Constellation residency layer; re-distilled 2026-06-12 from reference runtime/watchdog.cjs @ v2.5.87.)
@expansion temperature=0.2 model=agent/claude template=estreux/v0.0.1
@targets runtime
@profile supervisor
@state
wsConnected     : boolean = false   # board-role WS to server is up (= server alive)
backoff         : number = 1000     # reconnect backoff ms (cap 8000)
lastServerSpawn : number = 0        # last server restart ts (SPAWN_COOLDOWN gate)
lastBridgeSpawn : number = 0        # last bridge restart ts (SPAWN_COOLDOWN gate)
@ports
in   host       : string            # HOST; default 127.0.0.1
in   port       : number            # PORT; default 7878
in   serverPath : string            # SERVER_PATH; default server.cjs beside the watchdog
in   bridgePath : string            # BRIDGE_PATH; default local-bridge.cjs beside the watchdog
in   mainId     : string            # main agentId to expect in AgentList (MAIN_ID; default main-agent)
in   logPath    : string            # LOG_PATH; default watchdog.log beside the watchdog
out  restartServer() : detached-spawn server.cjs when server is down (cooldown-gated)
out  restartBridge() : detached-spawn the main bridge when AgentList lacks mainId (cooldown-gated)
deps ws         : websocket         # board-role connection used as a liveness probe
deps tcp        : net connect       # TCP reachability re-check before restarting server
deps spawn      : detached spawner  # spawn(node, file, {detached, stdio→log}).unref()
deps fs         : log appender      # watchdog.log
deps lock       : single-instance   # port-scoped PID lockfile (.watchdog.<port>.pid beside the runtime)
@behavior
singleInstance   : at startup (before any watching) acquire port-scoped PID lock .watchdog.<port>.pid — if the lock's PID is alive (signal-0 probe; permission-denied counts as alive), reject-new: log the conflict + exit(2). Dead-PID stale lock → auto-remove, proceed. Lock released on exit/SIGINT/SIGTERM (kill -9 leaves a stale lock for the next start to clean). Lock-setup I/O failure → WARN and proceed unguarded.
checkConfig      : at startup WARN (never silent-disable) for every unset env knob (host/port/mainId/serverPath/bridgePath — announce the fallback) and for a missing server/bridge file (spawn would fail; tells how to fix).
spawnDetached    : if target file missing → WARN + skip. spawn(node, file) detached, stdio appended to the log file, unref. Synchronous spawn throw → WARN, no crash.
connectWs        : construct WS as board role inside try/catch — synchronous construct failure → scheduleReconnect, return. onopen → wsConnected=true, backoff=1000, log "server alive". onerror → no-op (onclose owns recovery). onclose → wsConnected=false, ws=null, scheduleReconnect.
onAgentList(m)   : on pushed AgentList — if no agent with agentId==mainId → restartBridge(); else log ok. (server pushes AgentList on connect/disconnect change; no active polling needed.)
checkServerAlive : TCP connect host:port (2s timeout) → boolean.
restartServer    : if now-lastServerSpawn < SPAWN_COOLDOWN(8000) skip; else lastServerSpawn=now, detached-spawn serverPath.
restartBridge    : if now-lastBridgeSpawn < SPAWN_COOLDOWN(8000) skip; else lastBridgeSpawn=now, detached-spawn bridgePath.
scheduleReconnect: once-pending timer (backoff) → checkServerAlive; if dead restartServer; then ALWAYS connectWs (unconditional). backoff ×2 each schedule (cap 8000); reset to 1000 on onopen.
backupTimer      : every 15s — if !wsConnected, checkServerAlive; if dead restartServer (covers missed event path).
gracefulExit(sig): SIGINT/SIGTERM → log, ws.close, exit (lock-helper handler, registered first, releases the PID lock and exits 130/143).
@machine
# reducer: (guardState, event) → guardState
states: WATCHING(initial, WS connected) · RECONNECTING (WS down)
dispatch by event:
  WS_OPEN       : RECONNECTING → WATCHING     (entry: backoff=1000, watch AgentList)
  WS_CLOSE      : WATCHING → RECONNECTING     (entry: wsConnected=false, ws=null, scheduleReconnect)
  WS_CONSTRUCT_FAIL : * → RECONNECTING        (entry: scheduleReconnect — synchronous WS construct threw)
  agentlist_no_main : WATCHING → WATCHING     (entry: restartBridge, cooldown-gated)
  reconnect_tick : RECONNECTING → RECONNECTING (entry: if TCP dead restartServer[cooldown-gated], then ALWAYS connectWs; backoff ×2 cap 8000)
derive:
  no_interrupt ← only spawn a replacement when target is confirmed dead; live server/bridge untouched
  detached     ← all restarts spawn detached + unref → survive watchdog death (self-healing root)
  single_instance ← port-scoped PID lock at boot; duplicate watchdog rejected (exit 2), stale lock auto-cleaned, lock released on graceful exit
